raw_meta_yaml:
{% set name = "cwltool" %}
{% set version = "3.1.20231207110929" %}
{% set sha256 = "449f5bed0dc740184bafc44490d2674b5f34b2ae00b6851fddaf6900afd2293b" %}
package:
  name: cwltool
  version: {{ version }}

source:
  url: https://pypi.io/packages/source/c/cwltool/cwltool-{{ version }}.tar.gz
  sha256: {{ sha256 }}

build:
  number: 0
  skip: true  # [py2k or win]
  entry_points:
    - cwltool=cwltool.main:run
  script: CWLTOOL_USE_MYPYC=1 MYPYPATH=mypy-stubs {{ PYTHON }} -m pip install . --no-deps -vv

requirements:
  build:
    - python                                 # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - cross-python_{{ target_platform }}     # [build_platform != target_platform]
    - {{ compiler('c') }}  # for mypyc
  host:
    - python
    - pip
    - mypy ==1.7.1 # setup.py needs this when CWLTOOL_USE_MYPYC=1
    - types-requests
    - types-setuptools
    - types-psutil
    - types-mock
    - setuptools >=45
    - setuptools_scm >=8.0.4,<9
    - schema-salad >=8.4.20230426093816,<9
    - galaxy-tool-util >=22.1.2,<23.2,!=23.0.1,!=23.0.2,!=23.0.3,!=23.0.4,!=23.0.5
    - toml
    - argcomplete >=1.12.0
    - cwl-utils >=0.32
    - importlib_resources >=1.4  # [py<39]
    - ruamel.yaml >=0.17.6,<0.19
      # ruamel.yaml is needed for the type hints
      # the newer version: 0.15.99 has py.typed, which mypyc needs
  run:
    - python
    - setuptools
    - requests >=2.6.1
    - ruamel.yaml >=0.17.6,<0.19
    - rdflib >=4.2.2,<7.1.0
    - shellescape >=3.4.1,<3.9
    - schema-salad >=8.4.202304260938196,<9
    - prov ==1.5.1
    - mypy_extensions
    - psutil >=5.6.6
    - typing_extensions
    - importlib_resources >=1.4  # [py<39]
    - coloredlogs
